{"analytics_identifier":"OT1268","base_path":"/government/organisations/uk-council-for-internet-safety","content_id":"d78c6e86-da0c-4ff6-acb3-8b913136784a","description":"The UK Council for Internet Safety (UKCIS) is a collaborative forum through which government, the tech community and the third sector work together to ensure the UK is the safest place in the world to be online. UKCIS is part of the Department for Education , the Home Office , and the Department for Science, Innovation and Technology .","details":{"acronym":"UKCIS","alternative_format_contact_email":"","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The UK Council for Internet Safety (UKCIS) is a collaborative forum through which government, the tech community and the third sector work together to ensure the UK is the safest place in the world to be online.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"UK Council for Internet Safety\">UKCIS</abbr> is part of the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-education\">Department for Education</a>, the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/home-office\">Home Office</a>, and the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-science-innovation-and-technology\">Department for Science, Innovation and Technology</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":"department-for-culture-media-sport","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"custom","formatted_title":"UK Council for<br/>Internet Safety","image":{"alt_text":"UK Council for Internet Safety","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5bff1605e5274a0fcce06108/UKCIS_Black_200w.png"}},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"Policy paper","href":"/government/publications/digital-resilience-framework","image":{"alt_text":"UKCIS digital resilience framework","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d7a06e540f0b61c786baebb/s712_UCIS_Digital_Resilience_GOV_UK.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d7a0700ed915d51ea551530/s465_UCIS_Digital_Resilience_GOV_UK.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d7a06e540f0b61c7ba3b94f/UCIS_Digital_Resilience_GOV_UK.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2020-09-18T10:38:21.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>A framework and tool for organisations, policymakers, schools and companies to use to embed digital resilience thinking into products, education and services.</p>\n</div>","title":"Digital Resilience Framework"},{"document_type":"Research","href":"/government/publications/adult-online-hate-harassment-and-abuse-a-rapid-evidence-assessment","image":{"alt_text":"UK council for Internet Safety","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d13387b40f0b6350e1ab54d/s712_UCIS_OnlineHate2_L.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d13387b40f0b6350d6b533b/s465_UCIS_OnlineHate2_L.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d13387bed915d324443ba42/UCIS_OnlineHate2_L.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2019-06-26T09:30:01.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>A review of existing evidence on online harassment (including cyberbullying and trolling), revenge pornography and image-based abuse, and hate crime. The review highlights patterns of abuse based on age, sexual orientation, race and religion.</p>\n</div>","title":"Adult Online Hate, Harassment and Abuse: A rapid evidence assessment"},{"document_type":"Guidance","href":"/government/publications/safeguarding-children-and-protecting-professionals-in-early-years-settings-online-safety-considerations","image":{"alt_text":"Safeguarding children and protecting professionals in early years settings","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c58c2c2ed915d0422211b71/s712_early_years_gfx_960_640.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c58c2c2ed915d04148c30f9/s465_early_years_gfx_960_640.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c58c2c240f0b676d9455c76/early_years_gfx_960_640.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2019-02-04T21:40:00.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Guidance to help those who work in early years settings consider their practice and to take steps to safeguard both children and adults online.</p>\n</div>","title":"Safeguarding children and protecting professionals in early years settings: online safety considerations"},{"document_type":"Guidance","href":"/government/publications/education-for-a-connected-world","image":{"alt_text":"Education for a Connected World","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059e5140f0b6706e13b428/s712_Screen_Shot_2018-12-03_at_21.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059e51ed915d746ce208be/s465_Screen_Shot_2018-12-03_at_21.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059e51ed915d7466eee44e/Screen_Shot_2018-12-03_at_21.png"},"public_updated_at":"2020-06-30T09:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>A framework to equip children and young people for digital life</p>\n</div>","title":"Education for a Connected World"},{"document_type":"Press release","href":"/government/news/board-announced-for-new-uk-council-for-internet-safety","image":{"alt_text":"If it's unacceptable offline then it's unacceptable online","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059bf7ed915d74873e4b17/s712_Unacceptable_GOVUK.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059bf7e5274a6a6a534268/s465_Unacceptable_GOVUK.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c059bf7ed915d7455f5161d/Unacceptable_GOVUK.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2019-07-29T10:15:23.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Government has today announced the organisations that will sit on the Executive Board of a new national body to tackle online harms in the